Key Match Events: Travis Head hit a 19-ball fifty in his knock of 59, which included eight fours and four sixes
England lost three wickets in 10 balls to plunge to 113-7
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia was put into bat and dismissed for 179 with three balls remaining
The 23-year-old Cox was out for an unconvincing 17 off 12 balls
Overton was also in the top seven of an inexperienced and fragile batting lineup, and made 15
Australia’s fielding was brilliant, with Tim David’s catch — on the dive after turning round and running into the leg side — to remove Cox particularly standing out
